{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.31",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 31 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:10",
      "text": "Who shall find a virtuous woman? for such a one is more valuable than precious stones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:11",
      "text": "The heart of her husband trusts in her: such a one shall stand in no need of fine spoils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:12",
      "text": "For she employs all her living for her husband's good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:13",
      "text": "Gathering wool and flax, she makes it serviceable with her hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:14",
      "text": "She is like a ship trading from a distance: so she procures her livelihood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:15",
      "text": "And she rises by night, and gives food to her household, and appointed tasks to her maidens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:16",
      "text": "She views a farm, and buys it: and with the fruit of her hands she plants a possession.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:17",
      "text": "She strongly girds her loins, and strengthens her arms for work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:18",
      "text": "And she finds by experience that working is good; and her candle goes not out all night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:19",
      "text": "She reaches forth her arms to needful works, and applies her hands to the spindle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:20",
      "text": "And she opens her hands to the needy, and reaches out fruit to the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:21",
      "text": "Her husband is not anxious about those at home when he tarries anywhere abroad: for all her household are clothed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:22",
      "text": "She makes for her husband clothes of double texture, and garments for herself of fine linen and scarlet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:23",
      "text": "And her husband becomes a distinguished person in the gates, when he sits in council with the old inhabitants of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:24",
      "text": "She makes fine linens, and sells girdles to the Chananites: she opens her mouth heedfully and with propriety, and controls her tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:25",
      "text": "She puts on strength and honour; and rejoices in the last days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:26",
      "text": "The ways of her household are careful, and she eats not the bread of idleness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:27",
      "text": "But she opens her mouth wisely, and according to law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:28",
      "text": "And her kindness to them sets up her children for them, and they grow rich, and her husband praises her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:29",
      "text": "Many daughters have obtained wealth, many have wrought valiantly; but thou hast exceeded, thou hast surpassed all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:30",
      "text": "Charms are false, and woman's beauty is vain: for it is a wise woman that is blessed, and let her praise the fear of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.31.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:31",
      "text": "Give her of the fruit of her lips; and let her husband be praised in the gates.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
